            <h3 class="mont text-center" style="color:black;border: 4px double darkgray; padding: 10px;">Company Overview</h3>
            <h4 class="mont text-justify" style="line-height:35px;">

                Public Services Company (PSC) is one of the leading public services provider in the State of Kuwait. By order of His Highness late Amir Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber Al-Sabah, the Council of Ministers issued a decree No. 5/94 establishing PSC in 1996 as a closed Kuwaiti shareholding company, which was established in partnership between the public and private sectors and government agencies.
                <br /><br />
                The idea of establishing PSC was for the purpose of providing governmental services that the company can perform on behalf of a number of ministries and state institutions in a better and more effective manner.
                <br /><br />
                PSC manages several large projects for the Kuwaiti government represented in its ministries, regulatory bodies, citizens and expatriates among others. The projects are estimated to value KD 40 million with a staff of about 500 employees in the holding company and its fully owned subsidiaries.
                <br /><br />
                The Company offers its services within the State of Kuwait through its head office located in South of Al-Surra - the Ministries Zone Area, in addition 16 service centers distributed across all governorates in Kuwait. Additionally, we have international offices and branches to organize its joint projects with the Kuwaiti Ministry of Health for the expatriate manpower screening project, as the international branches are located in the Arab Republic of Egypt, the Republic of India and the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan.
                <br /><br />
                The Company also has contracts with the Ministry of Interior to provide technical support to all its service centers and departments, providing billing services and electronic payment solutions. In addition, PSC manages the employment contracts and the recruitment of specialized technical personnel for various ministries, for example with the Ministry of Justice and the Ministry of Finance, as well as a series of contracts with the private sector, specially the banking sector and investment companies.
                <br /><br />
                PSC launched XCEL Call Center, which operates several call centers for a number of clients both in the public and the private sectors, with a team of about 250 employees. The Company also manages Yemnak Concierge Project (Personal Assistant) which aims to achieve the highest level of luxury for its customers through meeting their needs, whether individuals or companies, by facilitating their daily lives 24 hours a day, seven days a week.


            </h4>
